or trends and debates since the 1960s, she illuminates the continuum of utopian thinking about higher education over time, revealing how it applies even in today’s climate of challenge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectiveszUnited States. 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectives. 0aSchool management and organization. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a20th century universities.  aamerican universities.  aclark kerr.  acollege curriculum.  acollege education.  acollege in america.  acolleges and universities.  aeducation history.  aeducation theory.  aeducational philosophy.  ahigher and continuing education.  ahigher ed.  ahigher education.  ahistory of universities.  aliberal arts education.  aresearch institutions.  aresearch universities.  aundergraduate curriculum.  aunited states history.  auniversity curriculum.  auniversity of california.  auniversity of chicago.  auniversity presidents.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027065740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095170940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951709423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951709/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY